{"lemma":"غَضارَةُ","slug":"غَضارَةُ","root":"غ.ض.ر","root_slug":"غ-ض-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ض-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31975"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of غَضَار (ḡaḍār, “clay”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"affluence, prosperity, abundance in life"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of small bowl"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31975","headword_ar":"غَضَارَةٌ","root":"gDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n., of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDura","text_ar":"غَضُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDira","text_ar":"غَضِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Used as a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ease, comfort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affluence; easiness of life: ampleness of the conveniences of life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the means of subsistence; plenty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plenty and prosperity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plentiful and pleasant and easy state of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDoraA='u","text_ar":"غَضْرَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (S.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahumo lafiY gaDaArapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُمْ لَفِى غَضَارَةٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlEayo$i","text_ar":"مِنَ العَيْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn AlEy$","text_ar":"من العيش"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY gaDoraA='i","text_ar":"فى غَضْرَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily they are in a plentiful and prosperous condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) Accord. to As, one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAda A@ll~`hu xaDoraA='ahumo","text_ar":"اَبَادَ ا@للّٰهُ خَضْرَا=ءَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbAd All~`h gaDoraA='ahumo","text_ar":"اباد اللّٰه غَضْرَا=ءَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God put an end to their prosperity, and their plentiful condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) but Ahmad Ibn- 'Obeyd says that both of these phrases mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God destroy the collective body of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and another says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their clay of which they were created."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$K","text_ar":"عَيْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lafiY gaDoraka","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَفِى غَضْرَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='i Eayo$K","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءِ عَيْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is in a plentiful condition of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino xayorK","text_ar":"مِنْ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lafiY gaDoraA='a","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَفِى غَضْرَا=ءَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is in an ample state of prosperity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  And, (O, K,) accord. to Lth, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaDaArapu","text_ar":"الغَضَارَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sand-grouse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (O, K;) but As disapproved this: (O:) [or] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaDoraA='u","text_ar":"الغَضْرَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaDaAriY~u","text_ar":"الغَضَارِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDaArN","text_ar":"غَضَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A4-  Of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDaArapN","text_ar":"غَضَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain utensil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"IDrd says, I do not think it to be genuine Arabic: (O, TA:) it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bowl such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSoEap","text_ar":"قَصْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": [app. from the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaAraho","text_ar":"غَدَارَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDaAy^iru","text_ar":"غَضَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}